quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,40,"It is not allowable [i.e., possible] for the sun to reach the moon, nor does the night overtake the day, but each, in an orbit, is swimming."
  36,41,"And a sign for them is that We carried their forefathers{1} in a laden ship.",1:[Usually meaning "descendants" or "offspring," the word "dhurriyyah" is used here to denote forefathers (their being the offspring of Noah), who were saved from the flood.]
  36,42,"And We created for them from the likes of it that which they ride."
  37,25,"[They will be asked], "
  37,26,"But they, that Day, are in surrender."
  37,27,"And they will approach one another asking [i.e., blaming] each other."
  38,4,"And they wonder that there has come to them a warner [i.e., Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ)] from among themselves. And the disbelievers say, "
  38,5,"Has he made the gods [only] one God? Indeed, this is a curious thing."
  38,6,"And the eminent among them went forth, [saying], ",1:[Planned by Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ) in order to gain influence and prestige for himself.]
